This is a simple implementation of a palindrome detector using the DFA approach. It follows the steps outlined in the problem description and provides a complete solution for the specified task.

The module definition includes parameter declaration for the width of the palindrome and input/output ports for synchronization and data flow. The main logic of the module consists of two states: MATCHING and NON_MATCHING. In the MATCHING state, the module checks if the current bit matches the next bit in the bit stream. If they match, the module enters the NON_MATCHING state. If they don't match, the module waits for the next cycle to repeat the matching process. Once the matching process completes, the module determines whether a palindrome has been detected or not by checking if the matched bits form a palindrome. Finally, the module outputs the result of the palindrome detection.